ortunities and potential acquisitions and performing early due diligence on potential acquisitions errol brings more than  years’ experience in the communications industry with broad expertise in the design development and successful commercial marketing of technologies for the internet and distributed networking community errol ginsberg founded ixia in  and took it from a startup to a multimillion dollar company that is a recognized leader in network testing he served as its president from  to  and its president and ceo from  to  from the early days of ixia’s founding errol ginsberg has helped shape the ip communications testing industry a visionary leader errol has overseen many of ixia’s innovations including multiuser highdensity platforms cpu perport interface modules and highproductivity testspecific applications his drive and vision helped forge ixia into its current position as a market leader errol became chairman of the ixia board of directors in january  before ixia he served as vice president of engineering at netvantage a network equipment manufacturer from november  to february  he served as an engineering consultant to netcom systems a test equipment manufacturer errol holds a bsee from the university of witwatersrand in south africa « brian davidoff partner at greenberg glusker chris silbermann founding partner of icm partners » general information contact us leadership donate the jel conference information program speakers tickets israel mission information sample itinerary testimonials faqs apply jgsi fellowship information speakers apply testimonials more programs d for  jel speaker series jlsa shabbat dinner jgsi summer cocktail hour the fall jewish grad mixer executive learning summer dinner series errol ginsberg  smart business magazine smart business magazine linkedin facebook twitter google youtube rss search for los angeles errol ginsberg by daniel g jacobs  am edt october    for errol ginsberg maintaining the culture of a company with more than  employees worldwide  particularly in the rapidly growing technology industry  is a particular challenge it’s not an easy task but you might expect a creative response from the president and ceo of ixia who named his company for a flower from his native south africa one way ginsberg he maintains the culture and makes sure employees stay focused and engaged is by showcasing their creativity on the company’s web site which features employee photos taken both on their travels and in their backyards his dedication to maintaining the company culture has paid off ixia a provider of performance test systems to ipbased infrastructure and services has gone from startup to  million in revenue in less than a decade smart business spoke with ginsberg about the importance of trusting your gut being flexible and knowing when to give up some of the control of your company focus on what you knowyou’ve got to have a very clear singular focus with very clear goals of what you are trying to achieve build sell etc that has to be very very clear very simple you have to go after that in an unwavering way as an entrepreneur you’re going to encounter all kinds of things where people will try to dislodge you or discourage you if you have a good vision and a good focus then you can stick with it then you can succeed move to new areas carefullyideally there will be somebody who is intimate with whatever that opportunity is who can help brief us on it you get together and review it and try to come to a consensus about pursuing that opportunity there’s a fair element of gut feel on these things you can do some analysis try to understand the market opportunity but a lot of these things don’t have that kind of data available you have to ask enough questions and at some point you make a decision a lot of times it’s based on prior experience which is really instinctive gut feel act sooner not lateryou don’t always realize you have a problem until it’s gone on for a while they become the bottleneck for the company they want to be involved in every decision every meeting they work  hours a day and it’s still not enough time they stifle the company’s growth you kind of know it when you’re having problems if you’re smart enough you hire people before you have those problems you think you’re doing ok but you’re missing deadlines on releases maybe the quality of your product isn’t where it should be you realize this isn’t working very well find natural leadersa person may have been a very good technical person was promoted to a position of management and failed miserably because they may do a poor job managing it could be because you didn’t give him the right skills or perhaps he just can’t get the respect of the people and the people don’t want to follow that person if people don’t believe in what you are saying and what you are telling them then you can’t lead anybody they have to believe in you to listen to you and follow you otherwise they are going to go around you make smart hiring decisionsat the end of the day you want to be careful about who you hire you want to hire the best people you can find the smartest people you can find and you don’t want to make a mistake  not just for the company but also for that person that person could be quitting another job and if we end up with the wrong hire it messes us up but it messes that person up too he’s in the wrong job it’s a mess for everybody be willing to change directiona company may run into difficulties along the way  market issues product issues the first thing is to recognize that change is needed once you know that you have to galvanize people explain the problem and set a goal that you can get people to believe in and then execute change is not always about building another product change can be somewhere within the company you may have organizational issues and you may have to deal with them acting on them quickly is a difficult thing sometimes you may have people that you’ve worked with for years and you start to realize that the company is outgrowing them you have to make a change that’s a difficult thing to do insist that employees use new systemsyou start off by saying we’d like to do this and use the system then we gave everybody training on the system you can’t just say ‘here’s the system go use it’ even though it’s relatively straightforward to use we trained the folks on it it still wasn’t effective what we had do is say then was ‘you will use this system’ at some point you have to be kind of forceful about it this is now an integral part of how we run this company once people started to understand they weren’t just entering things into a database that nobody cared about they started to take it seriously track salesfrom a sales standpoint we’ve actually done quite a lot we have a much more rigorous system for tracking sales opportunity we put in salesforcecom about two years ago we have gotten very effective in terms of how we use it they don’t like to be monitored in any way whatsoever that’s why they become salespeople they want that freedom of going about their day we don’t try to monitor their day but we do need to know what kind of opportunities they’re working on how to reach ixia   or wwwixiacomcom leave a reply cancel reply your email address will not be published required fields are marked comment name  email  website you might also likephani nagarjuna wants people who share his vision at nuevoraa hidden variable sparks rj lee group to strengthen customer relationshipshard vs soft skillschris rivielle has taken a different approach to employee development at plant constructiontubemogul was doing ok but brett wilson knew it could do even better errol ginsberg  malibu ca  intelius sign in we found errol ginsberg in malibu ca errol ginsberg intelius found that errol ginsberg is a male between  and  years old from malibu ca we have connected them to  addresses  phones and  relatives or associates also known as errol e ginsberg errol h ginsber